00:25:02,544 --> 00:25:05,045
There are basically four main types

363
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:06,266
of melee weapons in the game,

364
00:25:06,266 --> 00:25:08,027
and each of those four categories

365
00:25:08,027 --> 00:25:12,289
has three subtypes underneath those.

366
00:25:12,289 --> 00:25:13,530
And this is what those look like.

367
00:25:13,530 --> 00:25:14,591
So this is blade type one.

368
00:25:15,191 --> 00:25:21,393
It's a one-handed sword, and those are examples of the three different types of subtypes that go underneath that.

369
00:25:21,393 --> 00:25:27,214
This is Blade Type 2. It's a two-handed sword, and this is a pre-textured version of those subtypes.

370
00:25:27,214 --> 00:25:29,275
I promise they look a lot better now.

371
00:25:29,275 --> 00:25:36,897
And then there's Blade Type 3. These are blunts, so very handed to two-handed weapons.

372
00:25:36,897 --> 00:25:39,397
And those are the three subtypes for those.

373
00:25:39,397 --> 00:25:43,898
And the last one is the one-handed axe and the three subtypes in that family.

374
00:25:45,552 --> 00:25:49,275
So we thought that these could require a lot of content,

375
00:25:49,275 --> 00:25:51,397
and we're always cautious about these kind of things

376
00:25:51,397 --> 00:25:54,600
because more content means more audio,

377
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:57,182
and more audio usually means more things

378
00:25:57,182 --> 00:25:58,624
get loaded into memory.

379
00:25:58,624 --> 00:26:02,067
And Wonderlands is also releasing on last-gen consoles,

380
00:26:02,067 --> 00:26:02,788
so we have to be very.

381
00:26:03,268 --> 00:26:07,289
mindful and about that delicate of balance to the approach there.

382
00:26:07,289 --> 00:26:10,430
We played around with a procedural whoosh and loop system first,

383
00:26:10,430 --> 00:26:15,132
and the video on the next slide is a very interesting prototype of that

