00:27:14,972 --> 00:27:17,576
So yeah, they're all broken out

401
00:27:17,576 --> 00:27:19,279
into different types of categories

402
00:27:19,279 --> 00:27:21,001
and those whooshes.

403
00:27:22,087 --> 00:27:27,672
are very dull for the main subtype, but it gets more interesting when we add things like the

404
00:27:27,672 --> 00:27:33,376
shing layer or the spice layer. So the shing layer is basically the layer that a subtype inherits,

405
00:27:33,376 --> 00:27:35,938
and each subtype has its own unique shing layer.

